******
[2]
Date: Sat 16 Aug 2014
Source: Focus News Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2014/08/16/345817/bulgaria-requests-brussels-permits-it-to-vaccinate-ruminants-against-bluetongue-disease.html


Bulgaria has requested Brussels permits to vaccinate all ruminants against bluetongue disease, as the vaccine is strictly prohibited in the EU. Interim Deputy Minister of Agriculture and Food Georgi Kostov, who also chairs the established crisis staff over the disease, announced the news, the Bulgarian National Radio (BNR) reported.

The vaccinations will cost some BGN 7.5 million [USD 5.08 million], which the state will provide. According to the official, the effect the vaccinations will have will be felt next year.

